      <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
         <head>Biographical History</head>
         
      <p>Little is known of S. R. Rathbun.  According to <emph render="italic">Brigham's General Directory of Auburn, Weedsport, 
	  Port Byron, Union Springs, Aurora, Moravia and Cayuga, and Business Directory of Auburn</emph> (Wm. J. Moses, 1863), p. 50:</p>
	  
	  <p>The Auburn Woolen Company was organized as a corporation in 1846...In 1853...[it was] sold to private individuals, and 
	  after passing through several hands, in February 1863, again became the property of a corporation, of which  C. N. Fearing is 
	  President, William Gray Wise, Treasurer, and S. R. Rathbun, manufacturing agent.</p>
	  
	  <p>On page 69, the Auburn Directory section of the same volume gives his name as Samuel R. Rathbun.  His obituary appeared 
	  (possibly in the Rochester Democrat &amp; Chronicle) on August 9, 1888.</p></bioghist>
      
      <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
         <head>Scope and Contents of the Collection</head>
         <p>The S. R. Rathbun Account Book consists of a single large volume, listing income and expenses for the years 1865 to 1888. 
		 Payments from Auburn Woolen 
		 Company are listed regularly (e.g. "for six months services").  Other line items include "Church expenses," "Female apparel," and 
		 payments to S. R. Rathbun and F. R. Rathbun.  Banks (Cayuga Co. Bank, Auburn Savings Institution, Burlington Savings Bank, and 
		 others), insurance payments, and taxes appear regularly.</p>
		 
		 <p>Laid in on the first page is a single sheet, detailing an agreement between Augustus Dow and Reuben Rockwell regarding 
		 Dow's sale of his house to Rockwell.  The document is dated 1838.</p>
      </scopecontent>
      
